                                                                                                                                Containers and layout

                                                                                                                                Popover

                                                                                                                                Design beta

                                                                                                                                A popover is a small overlay container with a carrot that appears to display contextual information. Popovers usually appear when users interact with an element on the page and remain open until dismissed. Popovers can be presented modally and non-modally and customized to support a wide variety of short content.

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Changelog
                                                                                                                                Common alternative names
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Tooltip, toggletip, hover popup, helper, onboarding tip, guided help


                                                                                                                                Questions, comments, feedback?

                                                                                                                                Leave a comment in Figma or reach out to us on Slack.

                                                                                                                                #base-design-support


                                                                                                                                Usage

                                                                                                                                Use popover components to display additional information or options related to a specific element on the page. They can provide context-sensitive help, display related content, or provide a short list of options for users to interact quickly with.


                                                                                                                                Use for

                                                                                                                                • A small amount of content.

                                                                                                                                • Use when users require the popover open to reference other material on the page (non-modal presentation).


                                                                                                                                Don’t use for

                                                                                                                                • A medium or large content volume – consider a dialog or sheet.

                                                                                                                                • When content is simply a word or a phrase or displayed on hover –consider a tooltip.

                                                                                                                                • Error messaging (e.g., "Name is required").

                                                                                                                                • Feedback messaging (e.g., "Copied to clipboard").


                                                                                                                                Use cases

                                                                                                                                Disclosure
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Show contextual information related to an element.

                                                                                                                                Education
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Onboarding, tours, tutorials.

                                                                                                                                Popover versus tooltip

                                                                                                                                Tooltips are short and to the point, while popovers can be much more verbose. They can include content like a heading and more lines of text in the body, and additional controls.

                                                                                                                                Popovers need to stay open for users to interact with the content and controls inside.

                                                                                                                                In the case of education, tooltips are stand-alone introductions to new entry points and features, whereas popovers can provide multi-step guidance. They contain the ability to navigate through multiple steps with page controls and buttons.

                                                                                                                                Popover versus dialog

                                                                                                                                A dialog component should be used when you need to focus a user’s attention on an alert or choice related to a main task.

                                                                                                                                A popover component is only used to focus a user's attention to provide information on the focused element.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Don’t

                                                                                                                                Behavior

                                                                                                                                Popovers float above content after being triggered by a tap or click on an element like a button, link, menu, or icon.

                                                                                                                                • Popovers usually appear when users interact with an element on the page and remain open until dismissed. 

                                                                                                                                • Popovers appear near the object that triggered it.  

                                                                                                                                • Only one popover can appear at a time. 

                                                                                                                                • Opening and closing a popover depends on the use case.

                                                                                                                                • Popovers can be presented modally and non-modally with an overlay, depending on the use case. 


                                                                                                                                Education

                                                                                                                                Onboarding, feature tours, walkthroughs

                                                                                                                                (Modal presentation)

                                                                                                                                These typically appear automatically, triggered by an event in the system, like completing signup or logging in when a new feature is available. It can also be user triggered by tapping on a button like "get to know your safety toolkit" to start a tutorial. They can be chained together to allow users to move through a series of multi-step guidance. 


                                                                                                                                Disclosure (web only)

                                                                                                                                (Non-modal presentation)

                                                                                                                                Disclosure popovers open on demand when the user triggers them. Tapping or clicking on an element, like an icon or a button, reveals the popover.

                                                                                                                                To open with a keyboard, hit the  Enter or Space keys with the trigger focused. To close,  hit Esc or Tab out.


                                                                                                                                Dismissal

                                                                                                                                Popover requires a dismiss action with an X icon button or a text button like "Got it" Popover can be dismissed by interacting with a:

                                                                                                                                • Primary button to acknowledge the message, e.g., “Got it” or “Done”

                                                                                                                                • "X" icon button on the top right

                                                                                                                                • ESC on the keyboard or using an ESC gesture for screen readers  (supplemental)* 

                                                                                                                                • Overlay behind the Popover (supplemental) *

                                                                                                                                *An explicit text button or an "X" button is required besides the supplemental ESC, and overlay dismissal. Supplemental actions should not be the primary way to dismiss components, as it may not be intuitive to some users.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                If there isn't an X button, there must be a primary or secondary button to dismiss the popover.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                A popover cannot have no button to dismiss
                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                In a sequence of Popovers there are no options to dismiss by text buttons, therefore the X button must exist.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Do not force the user through a sequence of popovers. Every popover should have a way to dismiss.

                                                                                                                                Presentation

                                                                                                                                A popover presented modally blocks the surface behind it, allowing users to interact only with content in the popover until it is dismissed. Modal popovers have an overlay behind them to signal that the background is not accessible. Use when the background content doesn't need to be referenced to complete the task at hand.

                                                                                                                                Spotlight

                                                                                                                                In the context for onboarding, feature tours, walkthroughs, modal popovers can support a spotlight feature to bring focus to the item they point to. There can be 3 different shapes of spotlights use to focus on items of the screen. The shapes typically matches the shapes of the item. A rectangle shape with rounded corners can be used for tabs or tiles. The pill shape or sometimes circle can be used for buttons or smaller shaped elements. The edge to edge spotlight can be used for a larger item like a banner or card or a section of the screen.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Don’t

                                                                                                                                Motion and timing

                                                                                                                                Wrapping and truncation

                                                                                                                                Since popover is a container it's content will wrap to the next line. The popover container itself will only grow taller as the content wraps.

                                                                                                                                Breakpoint

                                                                                                                                Narrow view ports 599and below (mobile, mobile web)
